<paragraph blockId="10.[1042,1268,193,248]" box="[1083,1228,225,248]" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">
(
<figureCitation box="[1091,1221,225,248]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[114,158,2008,2029]" captionTargetBox="[117,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-89@11.[116,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 48–59. Thai post-tsunami Chironomidae. Polypedilum leei: 48, mentum, ventromental plate; 49, anterior thorax; 50, premandible. Mentum, ventromental plate: 51, Polypedilum ‘Thai sp 1’; 52, Polypedilum. nubifer; 53, Polypedilum (Pentapedilum) ‘K1’. Antenna: 54, Polypedilum ‘Thai 2’; 55, P. nubifer; 56, P. ‘K1’. 57, Dorsal head sclerites, P. ‘Thai 2’. Mandible; 58, P. ‘K1’, 59, P. ‘Thai 2’. Abbreviations: S3, cephalic seta 3; sc1, labral sclerite 1; vmp, ventromental plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333194" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333194/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">Figs. 48–59</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[836,1475,289,472]" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">
This most species-rich genus of 
<taxonomicName box="[1223,1384,289,312]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Chironominae">Chironominae</taxonomicName>
is very common in tropical waters, including those of 
<collectingCountry box="[1327,1425,321,344]" name="Thailand" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. The larvae of the genus require taxonomic study: there are many names, many species and different names have been used for the same organisms in different parts of the range. The current subgeneric system does not work for all larvae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[836,1458,513,536]" box="[836,1458,513,536]" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">Features that can assist in discriminating between larvae:</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[836,1475,577,696]" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">
Mentum (
<figureCitation box="[948,1132,577,600]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[114,158,2008,2029]" captionTargetBox="[117,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-89@11.[116,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 48–59. Thai post-tsunami Chironomidae. Polypedilum leei: 48, mentum, ventromental plate; 49, anterior thorax; 50, premandible. Mentum, ventromental plate: 51, Polypedilum ‘Thai sp 1’; 52, Polypedilum. nubifer; 53, Polypedilum (Pentapedilum) ‘K1’. Antenna: 54, Polypedilum ‘Thai 2’; 55, P. nubifer; 56, P. ‘K1’. 57, Dorsal head sclerites, P. ‘Thai 2’. Mandible; 58, P. ‘K1’, 59, P. ‘Thai 2’. Abbreviations: S3, cephalic seta 3; sc1, labral sclerite 1; vmp, ventromental plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333194" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333194/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">Figs. 48, 51–53</figureCitation>
): relative heights of teeth and evenness of size of increasingly lateral teeth; ventromental plates: relative dimensions, inner contour, medial separation and number of striae;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[836,1475,737,792]" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">
Mandible (
<figureCitation box="[958,1095,737,760]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[114,158,2008,2029]" captionTargetBox="[117,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-89@11.[116,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 48–59. Thai post-tsunami Chironomidae. Polypedilum leei: 48, mentum, ventromental plate; 49, anterior thorax; 50, premandible. Mentum, ventromental plate: 51, Polypedilum ‘Thai sp 1’; 52, Polypedilum. nubifer; 53, Polypedilum (Pentapedilum) ‘K1’. Antenna: 54, Polypedilum ‘Thai 2’; 55, P. nubifer; 56, P. ‘K1’. 57, Dorsal head sclerites, P. ‘Thai 2’. Mandible; 58, P. ‘K1’, 59, P. ‘Thai 2’. Abbreviations: S3, cephalic seta 3; sc1, labral sclerite 1; vmp, ventromental plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333194" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333194/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">Figs. 58–59</figureCitation>
): number of inner teeth, extent of pigment and size of outer tooth;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[836,1475,833,952]" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">
Dorsal surface of head (
<figureCitation box="[1102,1185,833,856]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[114,158,2008,2029]" captionTargetBox="[117,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-89@11.[116,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 48–59. Thai post-tsunami Chironomidae. Polypedilum leei: 48, mentum, ventromental plate; 49, anterior thorax; 50, premandible. Mentum, ventromental plate: 51, Polypedilum ‘Thai sp 1’; 52, Polypedilum. nubifer; 53, Polypedilum (Pentapedilum) ‘K1’. Antenna: 54, Polypedilum ‘Thai 2’; 55, P. nubifer; 56, P. ‘K1’. 57, Dorsal head sclerites, P. ‘Thai 2’. Mandible; 58, P. ‘K1’, 59, P. ‘Thai 2’. Abbreviations: S3, cephalic seta 3; sc1, labral sclerite 1; vmp, ventromental plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333194" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333194/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
): shape of anterior margin of frontoclypeal apotome, depth of any hyaline anterior submargin thereof, position of cephalic seta S3 relative to anterior and lateral margins;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[836,1474,993,1048]" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">
Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[949,1090,993,1016]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[114,158,2008,2029]" captionTargetBox="[117,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-89@11.[116,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 48–59. Thai post-tsunami Chironomidae. Polypedilum leei: 48, mentum, ventromental plate; 49, anterior thorax; 50, premandible. Mentum, ventromental plate: 51, Polypedilum ‘Thai sp 1’; 52, Polypedilum. nubifer; 53, Polypedilum (Pentapedilum) ‘K1’. Antenna: 54, Polypedilum ‘Thai 2’; 55, P. nubifer; 56, P. ‘K1’. 57, Dorsal head sclerites, P. ‘Thai 2’. Mandible; 58, P. ‘K1’, 59, P. ‘Thai 2’. Abbreviations: S3, cephalic seta 3; sc1, labral sclerite 1; vmp, ventromental plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333194" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333194/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">Figs. 54–56</figureCitation>
): relative and absolute lengths of segments and blade.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[836,1476,1089,1496]" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">
<taxonomicName authority="Freeman" authorityName="Freeman" authorityYear="1961" box="[836,1125,1089,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Polypedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leei">
<emphasis box="[836,1020,1089,1112]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">Polypedilum leei</emphasis>
Freeman
</taxonomicName>
is easily-recognisable amongst the regional species by the mentum (
<figureCitation box="[1237,1317,1121,1144]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[114,158,2008,2029]" captionTargetBox="[117,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-89@11.[116,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 48–59. Thai post-tsunami Chironomidae. Polypedilum leei: 48, mentum, ventromental plate; 49, anterior thorax; 50, premandible. Mentum, ventromental plate: 51, Polypedilum ‘Thai sp 1’; 52, Polypedilum. nubifer; 53, Polypedilum (Pentapedilum) ‘K1’. Antenna: 54, Polypedilum ‘Thai 2’; 55, P. nubifer; 56, P. ‘K1’. 57, Dorsal head sclerites, P. ‘Thai 2’. Mandible; 58, P. ‘K1’, 59, P. ‘Thai 2’. Abbreviations: S3, cephalic seta 3; sc1, labral sclerite 1; vmp, ventromental plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333194" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333194/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
) with all teeth more or less equal in size combined with a five-toothed premandible. The presence in the anterior abdomen of a sclerotised ‘crop’ (
<figureCitation box="[1042,1124,1217,1240]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[114,158,2008,2029]" captionTargetBox="[117,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-89@11.[116,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 48–59. Thai post-tsunami Chironomidae. Polypedilum leei: 48, mentum, ventromental plate; 49, anterior thorax; 50, premandible. Mentum, ventromental plate: 51, Polypedilum ‘Thai sp 1’; 52, Polypedilum. nubifer; 53, Polypedilum (Pentapedilum) ‘K1’. Antenna: 54, Polypedilum ‘Thai 2’; 55, P. nubifer; 56, P. ‘K1’. 57, Dorsal head sclerites, P. ‘Thai 2’. Mandible; 58, P. ‘K1’, 59, P. ‘Thai 2’. Abbreviations: S3, cephalic seta 3; sc1, labral sclerite 1; vmp, ventromental plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333194" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333194/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
, arrow) is highly characteristic, perhaps even unique. Larvae of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freeman" authorityYear="1961" box="[1191,1259,1249,1272]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Polypedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leei">
<emphasis box="[1191,1259,1249,1272]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">P. leei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurred in several site recovering from tsunami impact (314–1,847 µS. 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1422,1475,1280,1304]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">cm−1</superScript>
conductivity, 157–927 ppm), including three sequential samples from one site and also in the dilute, unimpacted pond (25–42 µS. 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1018,1070,1376,1400]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">cm−1</superScript>
conductivity, dissolved solids 13–21 ppm) in which 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Skuse" authorityYear="1889" box="[1008,1114,1409,1432]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Polypedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nubifer">
<emphasis box="[1008,1114,1409,1432]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">P. nubifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below) occurred. A pharate larva and a pharate female pupa confirms the identity and association.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[836,1481,1537,2040]" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">
<taxonomicName authority="Thai" authorityName="Thai" box="[836,976,1537,1560]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Polypedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[836,976,1537,1560]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">Polypedilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘Thai sp. 1’ has a mentum with relatively even tooth height, although the first laterals are lower than the medians and 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1043,1059,1600,1614]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">nd</superScript>
laterals, but not excessively so (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[114,158,2008,2029]" captionTargetBox="[117,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-89@11.[116,1455,191,1943]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 48–59. Thai post-tsunami Chironomidae. Polypedilum leei: 48, mentum, ventromental plate; 49, anterior thorax; 50, premandible. Mentum, ventromental plate: 51, Polypedilum ‘Thai sp 1’; 52, Polypedilum. nubifer; 53, Polypedilum (Pentapedilum) ‘K1’. Antenna: 54, Polypedilum ‘Thai 2’; 55, P. nubifer; 56, P. ‘K1’. 57, Dorsal head sclerites, P. ‘Thai 2’. Mandible; 58, P. ‘K1’, 59, P. ‘Thai 2’. Abbreviations: S3, cephalic seta 3; sc1, labral sclerite 1; vmp, ventromental plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333194" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333194/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
). The premandible has the typical two apical teeth of most congeners, but unlike 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Freeman" authorityYear="1961" box="[1157,1227,1665,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Polypedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leei">
<emphasis box="[1157,1227,1665,1688]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">P. leei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The larva resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[836,969,1697,1720]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Polypedilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[836,969,1697,1720]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">Polypedilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
‘B1’ figured in an Australian guide (
<bibRefCitation author="Cranston, P" pageId="10" pageNumber="241" refId="ref8904" refString="Cranston, P. S., 2000. Electronic Guide to The Chironomidae of Australian. http: // entomology. ucdavis. edu / chiropage / index. html. Viewed November 2006." type="url" year="2000">Cranston, 2000</bibRefCitation>
), with a ratio of the ventromental plate width to height near to three (108 × 38 µm) and with a distinctive rather elevated cluster of outer (5 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1122,1134,1792,1806]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">th</superScript>
–7 
<superScript attach="none" box="[1161,1173,1792,1806]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">th</superScript>
) mental teeth. However, the curvature of the ventromental plate of 
<emphasis box="[1250,1273,1825,1848]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">P.</emphasis>
‘B1’ is not evident in the Thai specimen, and conspecificity is unlikely. The single larva of this 
<typeStatus box="[1043,1089,1889,1912]" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">type</typeStatus>
occurred in an unusual pond which had water chemistry of 1,571 µS. 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1196,1248,1920,1944]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="241">cm−1</superScript>
and dissolved solids 786 ppm on the one occasion in which the larva was found, but although unimpacted. showed increasing conductivity with the passage of time.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5333194" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5333194" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5333194/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="242" startId="11.[114,158,2008,2029]" targetBox="[117,1455,191,1943]" targetPageId="11">
